A friend of mine said, &ldquo;It&rsquo;s for die-hard fans only.&rdquo;
He&rsquo;s right. Luckily, there are roughly seventy trillion die-hard FF7 fans. And I doubt they will be disappointed.
Advent Children is a DVD-movie about the events that happen two years after the events of the game. Some of the story-related parts might get you a bit sleepy, especially if you weren&rsquo;t particularly fond of the whole Reunion/Jenova/planet thing from Final Fantasy VII, but that&rsquo;s okay because&hellip;

Or so the paper says.
The Philippine Daily Inquirer had an article today about Oracle targetting local SMEs. Apparently they have an advantage because they use &ldquo;the Linux shareware.&rdquo;
Too bad I can&rsquo;t find the article online.

I remember the atmosphere at UP around the time of the infamous second evelope at Erap&rsquo;s trial. Even the normally apathetic Engineering students were being woken out of their political stupor by outrage at the turn of events by the Estrada-friendly senators. Everywhere you go in UP, people would be asking you if you were coming to the big rally on EDSA.
Today? Today, the conversations are like this:
&ldquo;Mag-gimik dapat kami bukas sa Makati eh&hellip; &quot;
